flavor_text_entries.red:
The tentacles are
normally kept
short. On hunts, they are extended
to ensnare and
immobilize prey.
flavor_text_entries.blue:
The tentacles are
normally kept
short. On hunts, they are extended
to ensnare and
immobilize prey.
flavor_text_entries.yellow:
Its 80 tentacles
can stretch and
contract freely. They wrap around
prey and weaken
it with poison.
flavor_text_entries.gold:
Its 80 tentacles
absorb water and
stretch almost endlessly to CON­
STRICT its prey
and enemies.
flavor_text_entries.silver:
In battle, it
extends all 80 of
its tentacles to entrap its oppo­
nent inside a
poisonous net.
flavor_text_entries.crystal:
When its 80 feel­
ers absorb water,
it stretches to become like a net
to entangle its
prey.
flavor_text_entries.ruby:
TENTACRUEL has large red orbs on its
head. The orbs glow before lashing the
vicinity with a harsh ultrasonic blast. This POKéMON’s outburst creates rough
waves around it.
flavor_text_entries.sapphire:
TENTACRUEL has tentacles that can be
freely elongated and shortened at will.
It ensnares prey with its tentacles and weakens the prey by dosing it with a
harsh toxin. It can catch up to 80
prey at the same time.
flavor_text_entries.emerald:
It lives in complex rock formations on
the ocean floor and traps prey using its
80 tentacles. Its red orbs glow when it
grows excited or agitated.
flavor_text_entries.firered:
It has 80 tentacles that move about
freely. They can sting, causing poisoning
and sharp, stabbing pain.
flavor_text_entries.leafgreen:
The tentacles are normally kept short.
On hunts, they are extended to ensnare
and immobilize prey.
flavor_text_entries.diamond:
With 80 tentacles for ensnaring
victims, it prevents escape until
the prey is weakened by poison.
flavor_text_entries.pearl:
It alerts others to danger by
stridently flashing the red orbs
on its head.
flavor_text_entries.platinum:
It extends its 80 tentacles to
form an encircling poisonous net
that is difficult to escape.
flavor_text_entries.heartgold:
Its 80 tentacles absorb water and
stretch almost endlessly to
constrict its prey and enemies.
flavor_text_entries.soulsilver:
In battle, it extends all 80 of
its tentacles to entrap its opponent
inside a poisonous net.

It extends its 80 tentacles to
form an encircling poisonous net
that is difficult to escape.

flavor_text_entries.omega-ruby:
Tentacruel has large red orbs on its head. The orbs glow
before lashing the vicinity with a harsh ultrasonic blast.
This Pokémon’s outburst creates rough waves around it.
flavor_text_entries.alpha-sapphire:
Tentacruel has tentacles that can be freely elongated
and shortened at will. It ensnares prey with its tentacles
and weakens the prey by dosing it with a harsh toxin.
It can catch up to 80 prey at the same time.
flavor_text_entries.sun:
Normally, it has 80 poisonous tentacles.
The longer one has been alive, the fewer
tentacles it will have.
flavor_text_entries.moon:
Although these Pokémon are rare, when a large
outbreak of them occurs, all fish Pokémon
disappear from the surrounding sea.
flavor_text_entries.ultra-sun:
It fires off ultrasonic waves from its red orbs
to weaken its prey, and then it wraps them up
in its 80 tentacles.
flavor_text_entries.ultra-moon:
It communicates with others of its kind by
lighting up the red orbs on its head. When
the orbs are blinking, it’s a warning sign.
flavor_text_entries.lets-go-pikachu:
Its 80 tentacles can stretch and contract freely.
They wrap around prey and weaken it
with poison.
flavor_text_entries.lets-go-eevee:
Its 80 tentacles can stretch and contract freely.
They wrap around prey and weaken it
with poison.
flavor_text_entries.sword:
When the red orbs on Tentacruel’s head glow
brightly, watch out. The Pokémon is about to
fire off a burst of ultrasonic waves.
flavor_text_entries.shield:
Its 80 tentacles can stretch and shrink freely.
Tentacruel ensnares prey in a net of spread-out
tentacles, delivering venomous stings to its catch.
flavor_text_entries.legends-arceus:
It has 80 tentacles, each with a venomous tip. These tentacles
are also extendible, lengthening when Tentacruel attempts to
catch prey. Use caution.
